o jazz and rock and roll. Robert Hornsby examines this remarkable and surprising period, showing that, even as living standards rose, aspects of earlier days endured. Censorship and policing remained tight, and massacres during protests in Tbilisi and Novocherkassk, alongside invasions of Hungary and Czechoslovakia, showed the limits of reform. The rivalry with the United States reached perhaps its most volatile point, friendship with China turned to bitter enmity, and global decolonization opened up new horizons for the USSR in the developing world. These tumultuous years transformed the lives of Soviet citizens and helped reshape the wider world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aNineteen sixties. 0aRussland. 0aSowjetunion. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074978640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300275063?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300275063423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300275063/original  a978-3-11-074978-6  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023